				<h2>The Beatles Blog</h2>

				<p>
					<b>From Liverpool to worldwide superstardom.</b>
					The Beatles formed in 1960 and forever changed popular music.
					John Lennon, Paul McCartney, George Harrison, and Ringo Starr
					combined unforgettable songwriting with groundbreaking studio
					innovation, making them one of the most influential bands in history.
				</p>

				<p>
					Throughout the 1960s, the band released a series of landmark albums,
					including <strong>Rubber Soul</strong>,
					<strong>Revolver</strong>,
					<strong>Sgt. Pepper's Lonely Hearts Club Band</strong>,
					<strong>The Beatles (White Album)</strong>,
					<strong>Abbey Road</strong>, and
					<strong>Let It Be</strong>.
					Their music continues to inspire artists and fans around the world.
				</p>

				<p>
					Although The Beatles officially disbanded in 1970, their legacy lives
					on through timeless songs such as <em>Hey Jude</em>,
					<em>Yesterday</em>, <em>Come Together</em>,
					<em>Let It Be</em>, and
					<em>Here Comes the Sun</em>.
				</p>

